No words, only understanding.  As his eyes closed, Devon placed his hands on Jerron's shoulders.  It was going to be difficult, to transport into a moving object, but he had a clear image of Derek's car, hopefully it would work.  He cleared his mind of all clutter, there could be no confusion.  Every aspect, his friends, the car, the dent in the side came forth.  In he felt the physical tug as he and Devon rematerialized in the car.  There was no suprise, they were getting used to his coming and going.  &quot;Hey everyone, Peru eh.&quot;  Derek explained the situation as the skyport loomed closer and closer.  &quot;So....we're basically just following a hunch?&quot; <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 356<br> <font color=#FF0000>(9/16/02 3:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=212>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ( just for the record)</span><hr size=1> Derek just stared. &quot;Well... yes. I guess. It's all we have to go on, right? If you want to leave, I'll hand over the keys.&quot; He knew it was a unnecessary offer. They'd go to the ends of the earth for Mika, especially Nefer. Might as well ask first, though.<br>
