Jerron sat alone.  He needed time to brood, as all did at times.  Lor is hurt, lor was hurt by this, this, BITCH.  He picked up his glass and mentally ordered a eight dollar glass of scotch.  A machine attached to the wall flew over and poured the liqour.  He took a sip before he threw the glass at the wall.  Glass shattered and the perfect white rug absorbed the amber drink.  He didn't care.  Within seconds a machine came by cleaning the mess.  How could this happen?  What did Lor do?  It was now that Jerron realized how little he knew about her.  He knew he loved her, he knew every little intricitacy about her thought patterns, but he doesn't know who she is.  &quot;Well, I'm going to.&quot;  Now on his feet, Jerron walked out of his bubble and into Derek's.  He didn't knock, didn't stop to acknowledge him, didn't even listen to what he said.  &quot;I'm going, you need me, call me.  Bye.&quot;  With that, he left.  His eyes were still closed, but the warmth he felt in his hand told him Lor was safe.  He was by her side, where he was meant to be, and where he will remain. <p>Ignis Summa Pugnabat, The fires shall cleanse the world.</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub95.ezboard.com/umindles.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Mindles</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Kay Oss kNite</span><br>  Posts: 411<br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/12/02 12:49 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub95.ezboard.com/ffantasystoriesforumfrm7.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=6.topic&index=218>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: ( just for the record)</span><hr size=1> Something woke Derek from the mini-nap he's just fell into. A femenine voice, he thought, but then again, maybe he was wrong. &quot;Hey, Derek. Are you awake?&quot;<br>
